Telco Customer_Who is going to leave or stay?¶

by Yeji Zoe Seoung

Investigation Overview¶

In this project, we investigated customers' behaviors, who is going to leave or stay? The main interest was the differences between churn customers and retain customers.

Dataset Overview¶

We explored Telco Cusomter Churn dataset containing 7043 customers' demographic information, customer's account information, and services that customers have signed up. Some features were needed to change its data types, but there were no missing values in the dataset.

Univariate Exploration¶

Main goal of this project¶

The main goal was to investigate what variables make differences between retain customers and churn customers. Even though 73 percent of customers continue to use the service, about 27 percents of customers decided to not use the service. One third of total customers are not negligible amount. We needed to figure out why they decided to quit the service.

In order to explore this, the first thing we needed to do was devided customers into two groups - Retain vs. Churn. Then, we investigated the differences between those groups.

Monthly Charge¶

We found monthly charge has a negative effect on churn customers. High payment made them decide to quit the service.

Conclusion¶

In this project, we investigated what features have an effect on the customer retent.

We found that customers who were using fiber optic for Internet service tend to end the service compared to those using DSL. We cannot conclude that Fiber optic for Internet Service might have poor service compared to DSL from this dataset, but in the further research, if we can get more information on like service satisfaction, Internet service quality, the price of those services, then we can find more why customers churned.

We also found that churned customers tended to be charged monthly more compared to retaining customers, and high monthly payment can be an effect on customers decision on retaining or not.

Churned customers are distributed on relatively new contract on the service compared to retained customers. Since they have less loyalty to the service, they easily decided to quit the service.

Interestingly, when customers contract on month-to-month, they are more likely to churn compared to those contract on year-contract.
